		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_355324">I have another question. I've been reading about WoW in a lot of places now (forums, websites, previews, beta reviews, etc.) and I am certain I read somewhere that when a group was killing monsters for a quest, and a quest item dropped, that *every* member of that group would get their own copy of the item. So indeed, if you killed Big Mr. X, he'd drop up to five heads, one for each of the members in your group (that has the quest active).<br />
<br />
I thought that was a great idea, and takes away the horrible camping areas over and over again for the rest of your group/guild (anyone done the shard camps and emperor key bits for the VT key in EverQuest, to name something? Then you know what I mean).<br />
<br />
However... reading the information topics on the WoW community site, I totally don't get the impression that this is actually how things work in WoW...  <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Frown" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
I'll quote one of these parts (taken from <a href="http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/info/basics/partytips.shtml" target="_blank">http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/info/...artytips.shtml</a>)<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Select your quests based on party size. If you can do the quest by yourself, don't waste time doing it in a party. Instead, spend time doing quests that you can't do without a party. You also might want to avoid quests that require each person in the party to collect a lot of parts. For example if the party has 5 members, and you need 20 items for each person, that ends up being 100 items you need to collect! You can complete that much faster by yourself or with a smaller group.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
So, perhaps (which I hope) the quoted text is old and they have changed the quest drop system since... or maybe the other way around?<br />
<br />
Could some kind beta tester(s) please tell me/us how these quest drops are currently working in the game as it is today in beta?<br />
<br />
Thankos Muchos! <img src="images/smilies/cool.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Cool" class="inlineimg" /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
